The paper deals with improving wireless security in a relay-assisted network using physical layer signal processing techniques. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the problem of secure transmission in the presence of eavesdroppers, which is a common concern in the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) relays and artificial noise (AN) also suggests a focus on system design and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves simulation results, which may fall under multimedia (cs.MM) if visualizations or other media are used to present the results.
